# ## 7. Vowel Tester
# ### Write a Python program to test whether a passed letter is a vowel or not
# #### Program Console Output 1:
# ##### Enter a character: A
# ###### Letter A is Vowel
# #### Program Console Output 2:
# ##### Enter a character: e
# ###### Letter e is Vowel
# #### Program Console Output 2:
# ##### Enter a character: N
# ###### Letter N is not Vowel

# In[75]:


def alpha(x):
    
    a=["a","e","i","o","u"]
    A=["A","E","I","O","U"]
    
    if x in a or x in A:
            print("its vovel")
    else:
            print("not vovel")


# In[76]:


alpha("A")


# In[77]:


alpha("e")


# In[78]:


alpha("N")


# ## 8. Triangle area
# ### Write a Python program that will accept the base and height of a triangle and compute the area
# ###### Reference:
# https://www.mathgoodies.com/lessons/vol1/area_triangle

# In[79]:


#A=(height+base)/2


def tra(height,base):
    area=(height+base)/2
    print("The area of triangle is  "+ str(area))


# In[80]:


tra(4,6)


# In[81]:


tra(10,2)


